sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh<br/>Controller
    participant Puller as model-serving-puller<br/>8084/TCP gRPC
    participant Pullman as pullman<br/>(Storage Library)
    participant Store as Remote Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant FS as /models<br/>(Local Filesystem)
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter<br/>8085/TCP gRPC
    participant TFPy as tf_pb.py<br/>(Python)
    participant Runtime as Model Runtime<br/>(Triton/MLServer/OVMS/TorchServe)

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 1: Model Load (Storage → Runtime)

    MM->>Puller: LoadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Puller
    Puller->>Pullman: Download model artifacts
    activate Pullman
    Pullman->>Store: S3/GCS/Azure/HTTP GET<br/>TLS 1.2+ / Storage credentials
    Store-->>Pullman: Model artifacts
    Pullman->>FS: Write artifacts to /models/{modelId}
    deactivate Pullman
    Puller->>Adapter: LoadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Adapter

    alt Triton + Keras H5 model
        Adapter->>TFPy: exec tf_pb.py (subprocess)
        activate TFPy
        TFPy->>FS: Read H5, write SavedModel
        TFPy-->>Adapter: Conversion complete
        deactivate TFPy
    end

    Adapter->>FS: Adapt model layout<br/>(runtime-specific directory structure)
    Adapter->>Runtime: Load model<br/>gRPC 8001/TCP (Triton/MLServer/TorchServe)<br/>HTTP 8001/TCP (OVMS)
    activate Runtime
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Model loaded
    deactivate Runtime
    Adapter-->>Puller: LoadModel response<br/>(model size, max concurrency)
    deactivate Adapter
    Puller-->>MM: LoadModel response
    deactivate Puller

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 2: Model Unload (Cleanup)

    MM->>Puller: UnloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Puller
    Puller->>Adapter: UnloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Adapter
    Adapter->>Runtime: Unload model<br/>gRPC/HTTP (pod-local)
    activate Runtime
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Model unloaded
    deactivate Runtime
    Adapter-->>Puller: UnloadModel response
    deactivate Adapter
    Puller->>FS: Delete /models/{modelId}<br/>(recursive cleanup)
    Puller-->>MM: UnloadModel response
    deactivate Puller

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 3: Runtime Status Check

    MM->>Puller: RuntimeStatus()<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Puller
    Puller->>Adapter: RuntimeStatus()<br/>gRPC plaintext (pod-local)
    activate Adapter
    Adapter->>Runtime: Health check<br/>(ServerReady / Ping)
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Status
    Adapter-->>Puller: RuntimeStatus response<br/>(capacity, max loading concurrency)
    deactivate Adapter
    Note over Puller: On startup: purge stale<br/>model files from /models
    Puller-->>MM: RuntimeStatus response
    deactivate Puller
